
This is the README file for p4est-0.3.0.
p4est is a C library to manage a parallel collection of quadtrees and/or
octrees.

See more documentation in the doc subdirectory.

Version 0.3.0 handles both 2D and 3D forests.

Version 0.2.0 includes libsc 0.5.0.  It handles the 2D forest.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example configure lines:

# GNU compilers, debug, default BLAS, splint syntax checking.
# Using an external libsc installed under SC_PATH.
#
configure \
        CFLAGS="-Wall -Wextra -Wshadow -Wno-unused-parameter \
                -O0 -g -rdynamic" \
        --enable-debug --enable-mpi --with-lint --with-sc=<SC_PATH>

# Intel compilers, debug, mpi, no builtin zlib.
# Default BLAS, VTK ASCII double output, splint syntax checking.
#
configure \
        CFLAGS="-Wall -w2 -Wcheck -O0 -g -rdynamic -wd869,981" \
        --enable-debug --enable-mpi --without-zlib --with-lint \
        --disable-vtk-binary --enable-vtk-doubles
